-h If the file is a symbolic link, change the mode of the link itself rather than the file that the link points to.
-i Removes the 'inherited' bit from all entries in the named file(s) ACLs.
-v Cause cchhmmoodd to be verbose, showing filenames as the mode is modified. If the --vv flag is specified more than once, the old and new modes of the file will also be printed, in both octal and symbolic notation.
